"If you do not create an Eversense account, functionality of the Eversense Mobile App is limited. You cannot share data with your health care provider via Eversense DMS, and you cannot share data with friends and family via the Eversense NOW remote monitoring app. All data and glucose values for the past 90 days are saved only to this mobile app and cannot be recovered if you replace your mobile device or delete the app. To learn more, read the Eversense CGM System User Guide for Germany available at global.eversensediabetes.com. Do you want to create an account?"

If you have created an Eversense account, you have the option to delete your account. If you delete your account, it is permanent, and you will no longer have access to your CGM data on the Eversense Mobile App, or in your Eversense DMS account. If you are using the Eversense NOW Mobile App, you will no longer be able to remotely view Eversense CGM data. You cannot use the same email address to create a new account. If you still want to delete your account, please contact your local Eversense customer support team.
